JO  - The Journal of Finance
JA  - The Journal of Finance
SP  - 213
EP  - 217
VL  - 38
IS  - 1
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0022-1082
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1540-6261.1983.tb03636.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - ABSTRACT This paper develops a new option pricing formula that pushes the underlying source of risk back to the risk of individual assets of the firm. The formula simultaneously encompasses differential riskiness of the assets of the firm, their relative weights in determining the value of the firm, the effects of firm debt, and the effects of a dividend policy with both constant and random components. Although this setting considerably generalizes the Black-Scholes [1] analysis, it nonetheless produces a formula via riskless arbitrage arguments that, given estimated inputs, is as easy to use as the Black-Scholes formula.
ER  - 

TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Optimal Pricing Policy of a Monopolistic Marketmaker in the Equity Market
AU  - MILDENSTEIN, ECKART
AU  - SCHLEEF, HAROLD
Y1  - 1983/03/01
PY  - 1983
DA  - 1983/03/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1540-6261.1983.tb03637.x
